				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Figured this would go better in balance than spells for topic, but they're dabbling with the new OoW pet heal on test.  If this is posted elsewhere just ignore the post--I checked but can't think of any reason anyone would really be interested in posting about the changes.  I also haven't checked the eqlive class boards, so not sure if it's being discussed there or not.  Before I start, this isn't another magician versus beastlords debate, but merely just a comparison of spells that to date may not even be near the same as they will be when Omens goes live <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />  
<br />

<br />
Now normally this wouldn't cause for much pause, given that this is just expansion spells being thrown around.  But, it's the exact changes they're implementing that made me perk my head a bit:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Renewal of Jerikor:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">07-02 22:50 Changed Casting Time from 7.0 seconds to 3.0 seconds</span>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">07-02 22:50 Changed Recast Time from 7.5 seconds to 10.0 seconds </span>
<br />
07-02 22:50 Changed Mana cost from 375 to 400 
<br />
07-02 22:50 Changed Slot 1 from "Increase Hitpoints by 1560" to "Increase Hitpoints by 1750" 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Note the cast time on the spell.  This leads me to believe that they're possibly going to think about changing pet heals in general for the class.  The problem is I don't really see it changing much about the dynamics of our pet heals, besides the idea of them simply being faster to deliver the heal, but longer recovery overall.  We'd still have to load two heals to get the job done, but due to recast there would still be the problem of keeping up with mob DPS.  
<br />

<br />
But there's another part that gave me pause--I started doing my normal comparison of Beastlord to Magician pet heals, and it dawned on me the change pretty much would make the two heals equal even though they work differently.  Here's the Beastlord pet heal, as it stands, on test:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Healing of Aulin</span>
<br />
  
<br />
Slot Description 
<br />
1:  Increase Hitpoints by 2730 
<br />
2:  Decrease Disease Counter by 16 
<br />
   
<br />
Mana: 531 
<br />
Skill: Alteration 
<br />
Casting Time: 9 
<br />
Recast Time: 2.25 
<br />
Fizzle Time: 2.5 
<br />
 
<br />
So faster recast, but a hefty casting time.  It's ~12 seconds roughly to deliver 2730 damage of healing power.  
<br />

<br />
But yes, these are test changes to spells that are no where near finalized.  But it does hint that <span style="font-style: italic">maybe</span> the devs are looking into our pet heals and dabbling with numbers to figure out what needs to be done to them (if anything).  It currently looks like they're envisioning the new heal to be a fast heal with long recast, allowing us to deliver a heal in a tight spot when needed.
<br />

<br />
I'm not even sure what point I was trying to make with this post, but I'd love to see our healing issues addressed and am probably reading too much into changes on test I am seeing.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=994568" taret=_blank>Impresario Sedenten Grey</a>
<br />
Maestro of Firiona Vie
<br />
<a href="http://www.fnfguild.com"><i>Fire and Fury</i></a>
<br />

<br />
-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Booperbustle on Wed Jul 07, 2004 4:16 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
