			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Dalren Fieryblade wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">They need to remove the recast time from our heals and lower all of our heals to 3 seconds.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
ok, so if they changed it to heal for 1750, with a cast time of 3 and a recast of 2.25, the resulting efficiency would be:
<br />

<br />
1750/5.25 = about 333/second
<br />

<br />
compared to the current beastlord Omens heal, which is:
<br />

<br />
2730/11.25 = about 243/second
<br />

<br />
That doesn't sound too fair to me, seeing as beastlords are half priest.  Now, what if you made Beastlords have the same upgrade to their Omens heal?
<br />

<br />
2730/5.25 = 520/second
<br />

<br />
While that may seem like too large of an upgrade for them, you also have to look at the mana cost...
<br />

<br />
Magician: 400/5.25 = about 76/second
<br />
Beastlord: 531/5.25 = about 101/second
<br />

<br />
So while they heal for more per second, they also use more mana per second.  Now, if you were to compare the healing-per-second to the mana-per-second of each spell, this is what you would find:
<br />

<br />
Magician: 333/76 = about 4.4 hit points healed per mana point, every second
<br />
Beastlord: 520/101 = about 5.1 hit points healed per mana point, every second
<br />

<br />
So yes, the Beastlord Omens heal would be more efficient than ours if these changes were made to both classes, but not by much.  And what can you expect from a half-priest class?<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
<br />
62nd level Arch Mage
<br />
Tunare Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
