				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On a side note:
<br />

<br />
Recently I've been trying to solo stuff in the tier1 god zones for BiC quest drops. In riwwi and qinimi I'm fine and got my pieces fast enough. Barindu and Ferubi were harder. With GoDS focussed RS and 64/60 pet heals chaining I could barely keep up, and burning pet mend if the mob had a few lucky hits.
<br />

<br />
A few days ago I got MS4 and seeing the prism skin I tried to take a different approach. Instead of chaining 2 heals I now chain Prot of Calliav and the 64 heal. I used MS4 in the hopes of the prism skin helping a bit.
<br />

<br />
So far I've been able to solo more effectively in Barindu then with RS and 2 heals. I'll be testing different approaches to this with maybe combining 2 calliavs in chain and 64 heal as backup and with RS and MS4 setups.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I must say it looks promising. Instead of just healing the pet we can use the calliavs to completely ignore a few hits. With a stun + high avoidance pet this will buy you a lot of time to wait for heal refreshes or nukes.<br />_________________<br /><a href="httP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39733">Arch Convoker Rhand Drago'Magica</a>
