			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">So by the same train of thought, Necromancers should get a huge pet heal for their pets, because their pets are undead and Necros are masters of the undead!
<br />

<br />
The justification of 'magicians are masters of elementals so we should be able to heal them better' doesnt quite work, from a game balance perspective or not.  Otherwise, after 65 levels and 400+ AA a magician should be able to "summon" an elemental larger than a piece of rock or a gust of air.  Why dont magician summon elemental dragons?  Or elemental giants?  Its all in the perspective of "masters of summoning" isnt it?
<br />

<br />
While I always agreed that magician pet heals were on the lacking side, I dont agree that magicians should heal their pets better than even the crappiest priest class.  Healing isnt part of the line-up.  So what if we have pets.  Let other classes heal them.  Thats what they do.  Magicians have always had heals but its nothing that compares to what a healer class can do.  Never has been, never should be.
<br />

<br />
Healing isnt an offensive ability, so while everyone croons about how magicians need to be balanced as a purely offensive class, you sit here and ask to be a better pet-cleric.  The only situation(s) that merit better healing are solo situations.  In a group, now especially with Pet Affinity, pet-healing is not something magicians worry about.  Soloing should have certain risks to it.  If a magician is about DPS, then why would he/she take time to heal his/her pet when its just as convenient to let it die and summon another?
<br />

<br />
Yes, yes I know.  You dont want your Virtue-buffed RoS to die.  Guess what?  Its going to die anyway, no amount of healing would stop that from happening, unless magicians become sole pet-clerics, and if that happens, don't you think developers will realize that magicians dont need bigger nukes or better efficiency nukes, because all they'll be doing is healing their pet-investments.  Let the pet kill the mob, while the magician heals.  Wow, this class has changed so much in 5 months.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thottbot.com/index.cgi?profile=P.Sanghem" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sanghem</a>
<br />
Fires of Heaven</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
