			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's all well and good that you think mages should get better heals from a roleplay perspective, but SOE doesn't look at it from a roleplay perspective.  They look at it from a balance perspective.
<br />

<br />
If you're still insistant on the roleplay aspect, I remember someone suggesting that mages should not get better heals, since elementals are complex beings.  You can't just throw in more earth energies to heal the earth pet, you have to assess the problem, and apply curative (as opposed to destructive) elemental energies to the area where the pet is injured.  This is harder with elementals, since they don't exactly bleed or have visible wounds.  Besides, beastlords are trained in the art of healing, magicians are not.
<br />

<br />
As for the realistic view, I would be happy if we kept our inferior heals and simply gained Healing Adept/Gift AA's, possibly with the Omens expansion.  I think this would solve the majority of our problems with healing, and besides, it's not like we're healing anyone else.
<br />

<br />
Kabreras, your suggestion reminds me of the beastlord warder buff back when SoL first came out.  Pet-only complete heal  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_doh.gif" alt="d'oh!" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
P.S.:  Have any of you soloers invested in an Improved Healing IV and Mana Preservation IV item?  If not, that may be a good idea, along with our summoned fastcast ring.  I would suggest the earring too, but it only works on detrimental spells.<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
<br />
62nd level Arch Mage
<br />
Tunare Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
